Shore Boulevard, east side, between 21st and 20th Avenues, showing a colonial type house, the property of R. A. Robertson is 1873-1891. A gas tank of the Astoria Light and Power Company is in the background. This area along the East River was at one time a favorite suburban residence district.

P. L. Sperr     View 1: June 3, 1927
